==Bannered routes==
===DE 404 Business===
{{Infobox road small
|state=DE
|type=DE
|subtype=Bus
|route=404
|location=[[Bridgeville, Delaware|Bridgeville]]
|length_mi=3.34
|length_round=2
|length_ref=<ref name=DelDOT/>
|formed=1999
}}
'''Delaware Route 404 Business''' ('''DE 404 Bus.''') is a {{convert|3.34|mi|km|2|adj=on}}<ref name=DelDOT/> long business route of DE 404 that runs through the town of Bridgeville. The route begins at DE 404 northwest of Bridgeville, heading southeast on two-lane undivided Seashore Highway through agricultural areas with some homes. DE 404 Bus. enters Bridgeville and heads through commerical areas, turning northeast onto Market Street and crossing Norfolk Southern's Delmarva Secondary railroad line. The route passes several homes before intersecting US 13 Bus. and turning south to join that route on South Main Street. The two routes run through more residential areas before leaving Bridgeville and heading through farmland with some development. The road widens into a four-lane divided highway and heads into a commercial area, intersecting US 13 and DE 404. At this point US 13 Bus. and DE 404 Bus. both end, with the road continuing southeast as DE 404.<ref name="DE 1999 map"/><ref name="google2">{{google maps |url=http://maps.google.com/maps?saddr=seashore+highway+and+newton+road&daddr=US+13+and+seashore+highway&hl=en&sll=38.724827,-75.588684&sspn=0.016238,0.042272&geocode=FchVTwIdvQJ--yk7hs68rvS4iTFRjkJsWGfiQA%3BFaPdTgIdrZR--ynPv8E9DvO4iTF2pSBbkqndEw&vpsrc=0&mra=ls&t=h&z=14|title=overview of Delaware Route 404 Business|accessdate=November 16, 2011}}</ref> DE 404 Bus. was created in 1999 when DE 404 was rerouted to bypass Bridgeville on the alignment of DE 404 Alt.<ref name="DE 1999 map"/>
{{-}}

===Former DE 404 Alternate===
{{Infobox road small
|state=DE
|type=DE
|subtype=Alt
|route=404
|location=[[Bridgeville, Delaware|Bridgeville]]
|length_mi=4.65
|length_round=2
|length_ref=<ref name=DelDOT/>
|formed=1990
|deleted=1999
}}
'''Delaware Route 404 Alternate''' ('''DE 404 Alt.''') was a {{convert|4.65|mi|km|2|adj=on}}<ref name=DelDOT/> alternate alignment of DE 404 that bypassed the town of Bridgeville. It ran to the north of Bridgeville on Newton Road and to the east of Bridgeville on US 13.<ref name="DE 1997 map">{{Delaware road map|year=1997}}</ref><ref name="google3">{{google maps |url=http://maps.google.com/maps?saddr=seashore+highway+and+newton+road&daddr=38.762,-75.60653+to:US+13+and+seashore+highway&hl=en&sll=38.754846,-75.603018&sspn=0.032463,0.084543&geocode=FchVTwIdvQJ--yk7hs68rvS4iTFRjkJsWGfiQA%3BFRB2TwId_lV--ynfFqz1sYy4iTEFUFvO7iWjyQ%3BFaPdTgIdrZR--ynPv8E9DvO4iTF2pSBbkqndEw&vpsrc=0&mra=ls&via=1&t=h&z=13|title=overview of Delaware Route 404 Alternate|accessdate=November 16, 2011}}</ref> The route was created by 1990.<ref name="DE 1990 map"/> The alignment of DE 404 Alt.was replaced by DE 404 itself in 1999. The route of DE 404 in Bridgeville then became known as DE 404 Bus.<ref name="DE 1999 map"/>
{{-}}

